ith a K-class star that\ndominates its spectrum. ASASSN-14ei and ASASSN-14mv both show a remarkable\nnumber of echo outbursts following superoutbursts (13 and 10 echo outbursts\nrespectively). ASASSN-14ei shows an increased outburst rate over the years\nfollowing its superoutburst, perhaps resulting from an increased accretion\nrate.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Tue, 26 May 2020 10:33:52 GMT"}],"update_date":"2020-06-10"}
